    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Compound known as a hygroscopic, blue-gray powder that occurs naturally as the mineral "vivianite (mineral)." Used in the pigment "blue ocher"; has been found in Roman paint residues. Ferrous phosphate is also used as a colorant in ceramics.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
